Date:10/18/2011 6:20:20 PM
From:J Mako
re: GLW and China

While I'm bullish on GLW, I do have a contrarian-contrarian thought on GLW's
medium-term prospect.

Research houses forecast demand of LCD panels will be flat in 2012. The slow
down in western countries will be picked up by the growth in Asian countries.
Apparently, the biggest factor here is China. GLW voted with its wallet by
building factories in China.

Can we count on growing consumption in China? China's recent growth has been
fueled by MASSIVE investment which has caused HUGE capital misallocation. Can
China shifts from an investment-driven economy to a consumption economy? That
requires increasing their wage level, which in turn requires a bet-the-country
correction to their capital misallocation. Will that happen? As we now know,
Japan tried but got into its lost decade.

I don't have further insight. But I can point you to this excellent article:

http://www.iifunds.com.au/bristlemouth/china%E2%80%99s-boom-it-won%E2%80%99t-la
t-it-won%E2%80%99t-end-now
%EOM----------------------

