From:Shane M
armi, the cloud vs. consumer device is very difficult thing for me to see. INTC
results argue that the behind the scenes needed to power the cloud that makes
all these little consumer devices work is very healthy and growing - even
though it's somewhat out of sight. Understanding the branching / divergence of
cloud / consumer device makes understanding the different technical needs
important in picking winners/losers. I'm not there yet, but I'm thinking two
entirely different ecosystems could result due to extremely different end user
requirements - at least much more difference than we've seen in the past.

anyhow my $0.02 as I try to understand what's happening longer term. long intc,
msft, and wdc looked cheap to me before the floods. I've owned wdc in the past
and will continue to have an eye open for wdc in the future - it's priced for
near term obsolescence, and this is a good mgmt team that has capacity to adapt
evolve. all imho
